definition.value: The tub gurnard, *Chelidonichthys lucerna* (also C. lucernus, Trigla lucerna, T. corax) is a species of bottom-dwelling coastal fish with a spiny armored head and fingerlike pectoral fins used for crawling along the sea bottom. The tub gurnard is a reddish fish with blue pectoral fins.  [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tub_gurnard]
An evergreen tropical tree in the flowering plant family Myrtaceae.

*Ugni molinae*, commonly known as Chilean guava, or strawberry myrtle, is a shrub native to Chile and adjacent regions of southern Argentina. The fruit is sometimes marketed as "Ugniberry", as "New Zealand cranberry" in New Zealand, and the name "Tazziberry" has been trademarked in Australia, but it is not a native plant to these countries. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ugni_molinae]
